document_data.History:
When the [[dwarves]] of [[Besilmer]] constructed the [[Halls of the Hunting Axe]], they built a complex array of machinery in order to ensure that the tomb of [[Torhild Flametongue]] would remain hidden. This included four large, stone flywheels that each sported an axle and were connected to a series of gears. Upon each axle was a sprocket, which could be slid along to engage a different part of the machinery.

During the time of the [[Everlasting Rime]], a [[gnome]] [[artificer]] by the name of [[Doxi Whirglitz]] constructed a clockwork [[knucklehead trout]], a [[construct]] whose design featured sprockets.<ref>{{Cite adventurers league/The Great Knucklehead Rally|7}}

When a group of [[adventurer]]s came to the Halls of the Hunting Axe in [[1491 DR]], they had to manipulate those sprockets in order to gain access to Tormhild's decoy tomb.
